HEADWORD: Brassart
<hw>Bras"sart</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>brassard</ets>, fr. <ets>bras</ets> arm. See <er>Brace</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Armor for the arm; -- generally used for the
whole arm from the shoulder to the wrist, and consisting, in the 15th
and 16th centuries, of many parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

